rComments: I really enjoyed this class and I loved Janie as a prof. We had 2 anatomy quizzes, a lab exam, a midterm, a final exam, and a group project with 3 parts. All her exams and quizzes were very fair. Plus, the lab exam and midterm were open book and had no time limit. The labs were really fun too especially the taping ones.

Favorite prof I've had so far. Exams are fair and on the actual course material. Wants her students to succeed in every way possible. Will take extra time to explain concepts even though all the information you need to succeed is in her slides. The lab section of this course is super practical and really helps to solidify what we've learned. 10/10.
Great prof and so far been an easy A. Lab's kinda confusing when learning by watching videos, as videos taken are horrible angles and hard to see. Good prof and would take again

I have her for 3120 and 3125; she's by far my absolute favourite prof I've ever had. She answers her emails right away, explains content until most students are comfortable with it, offers extensions if desperately needed, exams really test your knowledge; the list of positives never end. I wish I had her for all my classes. I've learned so much

While the course itself is pretty difficult, Janies a sweetheart and makes sure students are 100% prepared for tests and quizzes as long as they watch lectures and put the work in. A lot of online classes can feel very impersonal, direct, and boring, this class was an exception. Definitely take her class if you can.

Everything is straight forward in this class. She made it enjoyable even online. No homework. Most of the work is done alone as its anatomy so its really up to you. Class is nicely scheduled and gives enough time to learn. Lab is easy too just honestly a lot of memorization but fun if you love anatomy.
Such a caring professor who genuinely wants you to succeed. Course is a little content heavy with lots of memorizing, but professor Janie makes it engaging and interesting. Choose her if you can!!

Possibly my favorite prof I've encountered in university so far. Not only is the class interesting and gives you many opportunities to do well, but the project has extremely clear grading criteria. Janie is extremely compassionate with all her students and makes sure everyone is doing well and that everyone is okay with deadlines, etc. Fun lab too!

This prof is very caring and is always available to help you. This class is difficult and you need to start studying day 1. The course material is very straight forward. It is a learn everything by heart class. The prof will give you a lot of pointers for what to expect on exams. The lab for this class is extremely hard but forces you to study.
